The paper deals with a numerically stable and differentiable approach to leveraging eigenvectors in deep networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG and cs.CV). The paper also discusses ZCA whitening and PCA denoising, which are normalization strategies for deep networks, and thus could fall under the sub-categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper introduces a new normalization strategy for deep networks, which could also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
